    "value": "[{\"name\":\"\",\"price\":\"$35 /yr\",\"description\":\"The SkyHigh Paragliding Club is very keen to help new pilots in their first years of flying. The Club has a nominated Novice Pilot Representative who will organise specific events and provide all sorts of help to new pilots. Please see our Safety Guidelines.\\n\\nIf you don't yet have a Paragliding Pilot License, check out the Training section for a list of License Courses.\\n\\nPlease remember, to fly anywhere in Australia all paragliding pilots must have a valid paragliding license (accredited by a registered CFI) and be a current member of the Sports Aviation Federation Australia (SAFA).  SAFA membership will be automatically checked after payment.\",\"features\":[\"\"]},{\"name\":\"Non-flying Member\",\"price\":\"$0 /Yr\",\"description\":\"SkyHigh welcomes Non-Flying Members. This is useful for those pilots who may not be able to fly for reasons such as injury or for those who would like to join the Club to participate in its social events. Non-flying members cannot participate in club flying events as a pilot.\",\"features\":[\"Non-flying members cannot participate in club flying events as a pilot.\"]}]"
